#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya25, sc91
msgctxt "mn38:25.1"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhikkhave, upanītā kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, iminā sandiṭṭhikena dhammena akālikena ehipassikena opaneyyikena paccattaṃ veditabbena viññūhi. "
msgstr "“Good, mendicants! You have been guided by me with this teaching that’s visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

msgctxt "mn38:25.2"
msgid "Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhi—"
msgstr "For when I said that this teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves, "

msgctxt "mn38:25.3"
msgid "iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttanti. "
msgstr "this is what I was referring to. "

# NOTE: BB’s “womb” here is incorrect; he fixes this in AN 3.61.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya26, pts-vp-pli1.266, sc92
msgctxt "mn38:26.1"
msgid "Tiṇṇaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sannipātā gabbhassāvakkanti hoti. "
msgstr "Mendicants, when three things come together an embryo is conceived. "

msgctxt "mn38:26.2"
msgid "Idha mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca na utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca na paccupaṭṭhito hoti, neva tāva gabbhassāvakkanti hoti. "
msgstr "In a case where the mother and father come together, but the mother is not in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, and the spirit being reborn is not present, the embryo is not conceived. "

msgctxt "mn38:26.3"
msgid "Idha mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca na paccupaṭṭhito hoti, neva tāva gabbhassāvakkanti hoti. "
msgstr "In a case where the mother and father come together, the mother is in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, but the spirit being reborn is not present, the embryo is not conceived. "

msgctxt "mn38:26.4"
msgid "Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca paccupaṭṭhito hoti—evaṃ tiṇṇaṃ sannipātā gabbhassāvakkanti hoti. "
msgstr "But when these three things come together—the mother and father come together, the mother is in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, and the spirit being reborn is present—an embryo is conceived. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: This use of samsaya is unusual. Comm says “Saṃsayenāti ‘‘arogo nu kho bhavissāmi ahaṃ vā, putto vā me’’ti evaṃ mahantena jīvitasaṃsayena” For jivitasamsaya and pranasamsaya, Skt has “risk to life”. The term appears at Bi Pc 61, where garubhara is an adjective (garubhārā ayyā = the lady is heavy with child). Nowhere, apparently, is the term glossed in the comm. This passage is also missing in Cone and PTS dict, though perhaps they do not treat it as a compound.
#. REF: nya27
#. VAR: garubhāraṃ → garumbhāraṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn38:27.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, mātā nava vā dasa vā māse gabbhaṃ kucchinā pariharati mahatā saṃsayena garubhāraṃ. "
msgstr "The mother nurtures the embryo in her womb for nine or ten months at great risk to her heavy burden. "

msgctxt "mn38:27.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, mātā navannaṃ vā dasannaṃ vā māsānaṃ accayena vijāyati mahatā saṃsayena garubhāraṃ. "
msgstr "When nine or ten months have passed, the mother gives birth at great risk to her heavy burden. "

msgctxt "mn38:27.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jātaṃ samānaṃ sakena lohitena poseti. "
msgstr "When the infant is born she nourishes it with her own blood. "

msgctxt "mn38:27.4"
msgid "Lohitañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye yadidaṃ mātuthaññaṃ. "
msgstr "For mother’s milk is regarded as blood in the training of the noble one. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya28
msgctxt "mn38:28.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhikkhave, kumāro vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya "
msgstr "That boy grows up and his faculties mature. "

msgctxt "mn38:28.2"
msgid "yāni tāni kumārakānaṃ kīḷāpanakāni tehi kīḷati, seyyathidaṃ—vaṅkakaṃ ghaṭikaṃ mokkhacikaṃ ciṅgulakaṃ pattāḷhakaṃ rathakaṃ dhanukaṃ. "
msgstr "He accordingly plays childish games such as toy plows, tipcat, somersaults, pinwheels, toy measures, toy carts, and toy bows. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29, sc93
msgctxt "mn38:29.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhikkhave, kumāro vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya "
msgstr "That boy grows up and his faculties mature further. "

msgctxt "mn38:29.2"
msgid "pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti—"
msgstr "He accordingly amuses himself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "mn38:29.3"
msgid "cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi, "
msgstr "Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:29.4"
msgid "sotaviññeyyehi saddehi … "
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:29.5"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi … "
msgstr "Smells known by the nose … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:29.6"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi … "
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:29.7"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi. "
msgstr "Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

# NOTE: Note that SN in parallels for this passage has adhimuccati rather than sarajjati.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya30, pts-vp-pli1.267, sc94
msgctxt "mn38:30.1"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe sārajjati, appiyarūpe rūpe byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati parittacetaso. "
msgstr "When they see a sight with their eyes, if it’s pleasant they desire it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body unestablished and their heart restricted. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.2"
msgid "Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.3"
msgid "So evaṃ anurodhavirodhaṃ samāpanno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "Being so full of favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī. "
msgstr "This gives rise to relishing. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.5"
msgid "Yā vedanāsu nandī tadupādānaṃ, tassupādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Relishing feelings is grasping. Their grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.6"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.7"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.8"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.9"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.10"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.11"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme sārajjati, appiyarūpe dhamme byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati parittacetaso. "
msgstr "When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they desire it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body unestablished and their heart restricted. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.12"
msgid "Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:30.13"
msgid "So evaṃ anurodhavirodhaṃ samāpanno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "Being so full of favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.14"
msgid "Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato uppajjati nandī. "
msgstr "This gives rise to relishing. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.15"
msgid "Yā vedanāsu nandī tadupādānaṃ, tassupādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Relishing feelings is grasping. Their grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "mn38:30.16"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya31, sc95
msgctxt "mn38:31.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā. "
msgstr "But consider when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed. "

msgctxt "mn38:31.2"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "mn38:31.3"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ; "
msgstr "He proclaims a teaching that is good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, with the right meaning and phrasing. "

msgctxt "mn38:31.4"
msgid "kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He reveals an entirely full and pure spiritual life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya32
msgctxt "mn38:32.1"
msgid "Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto. "
msgstr "A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some good family. "

msgctxt "mn38:32.2"
msgid "So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati. "
msgstr "They gain faith in the Realized One, "

msgctxt "mn38:32.3"
msgid "So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "and reflect, "

msgctxt "mn38:32.4"
msgid "‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā. "
msgstr "‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open. "

msgctxt "mn38:32.5"
msgid "Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ. "
msgstr "It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell. "

msgctxt "mn38:32.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā, kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I cut off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from lay life to homelessness?’ "

msgctxt "mn38:32.7"
msgid "So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā, kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati. "
msgstr "After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya33, sc96
msgctxt "mn38:33.1"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati. "
msgstr "Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.268, sc97
msgctxt "mn38:33.2"
msgid "Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati. "
msgstr "They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc98
msgctxt "mn38:33.3"
msgid "Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti, ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā. "
msgstr "They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc99
msgctxt "mn38:33.4"
msgid "Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa. "
msgstr "They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc100
msgctxt "mn38:33.5"
msgid "Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī, samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc101
msgctxt "mn38:33.6"
msgid "Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc102
msgctxt "mn38:33.7"
msgid "Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena, sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ. "
msgstr "They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc103
msgctxt "mn38:33.8"
msgid "So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "They avoid injuring plants and seeds. "

msgctxt "mn38:33.9"
msgid "ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato, virato vikālabhojanā. "
msgstr "They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time. "

msgctxt "mn38:33.10"
msgid "Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows. "

msgctxt "mn38:33.11"
msgid "mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "They avoid beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, perfumes, and makeup. "

msgctxt "mn38:33.12"
msgid "uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "They avoid high and luxurious beds. "

msgctxt "mn38:33.13"
msgid "jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "They avoid receiving gold and money, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.14"
msgid "āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "raw grains, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.15"
msgid "āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "raw meat, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.16"
msgid "itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "women and girls, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.17"
msgid "dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "male and female bondservants, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.18"
msgid "ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "goats and sheep, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.19"
msgid "kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "chickens and pigs, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.20"
msgid "hatthigavāssavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "elephants, cows, horses, and mares, "

msgctxt "mn38:33.21"
msgid "khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "and fields and land. "

msgctxt "mn38:33.22"
msgid "dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "They avoid running errands and messages; "

msgctxt "mn38:33.23"
msgid "kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "buying and selling; "

msgctxt "mn38:33.24"
msgid "tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "falsifying weights, metals, or measures; "

msgctxt "mn38:33.25"
msgid "ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti, "
msgstr "bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity; "

msgctxt "mn38:33.26"
msgid "chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti. "
msgstr "mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya34, pts-vp-pli1.269, sc104
msgctxt "mn38:34.1"
msgid "So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati. "
msgstr "They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things. "

msgctxt "mn38:34.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti sapattabhārova ḍeti; "
msgstr "They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden. "

msgctxt "mn38:34.3"
msgid "evameva bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena, kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things. "

msgctxt "mn38:34.4"
msgid "So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya35, sc105
msgctxt "mn38:35.1"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī. "
msgstr "When they see a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details. "

msgctxt "mn38:35.2"
msgid "Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:35.3"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:35.4"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:35.5"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:35.6"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:35.7"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī. "
msgstr "When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details. "

msgctxt "mn38:35.8"
msgid "Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint. "

msgctxt "mn38:35.9"
msgid "So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya36, sc106
msgctxt "mn38:36.1"
msgid "So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti. "
msgstr "They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya37, sc107
#. VAR: imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato → etthantare pāṭho sī, syā1-3 potthakesu natthi, 9M:1042; 10M:20, 10M:1289; 11M:44; 15A4:1264; 31Pu:449
msgctxt "mn38:37.1"
msgid "So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato, "
msgstr "When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness, "

msgctxt "mn38:37.2"
msgid "vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati—araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ. "
msgstr "they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya38
msgctxt "mn38:38.1"
msgid "So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya, parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there. "

msgctxt "mn38:38.2"
msgid "So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti; "
msgstr "Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire. "

msgctxt "mn38:38.3"
msgid "byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti; "
msgstr "Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will. "

msgctxt "mn38:38.4"
msgid "thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī, sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti; "
msgstr "Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness. "

msgctxt "mn38:38.5"
msgid "uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti; "
msgstr "Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse. "

msgctxt "mn38:38.6"
msgid "vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti. "
msgstr "Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya39, pts-vp-pli1.270, sc108
msgctxt "mn38:39.1"
msgid "So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe, "
msgstr "They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn38:39.2"
msgid "vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn38:39.3"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "mn38:39.4"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "mn38:39.5"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya40, pts-vp-pli1.271, sc109
msgctxt "mn38:40.1"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe na sārajjati, appiyarūpe rūpe na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso. "
msgstr "When they see a sight with their eyes, if it’s pleasant they don’t desire it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "mn38:40.2"
msgid "Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:40.3"
msgid "So evaṃ anurodhavirodhavippahīno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti, sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "Having given up favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they don’t approve, welcome, or keep clinging to it. "

msgctxt "mn38:40.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato yā vedanāsu nandī sā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "As a result, relishing of feelings ceases. "

msgctxt "mn38:40.5"
msgid "Tassa nandīnirodhā upādānanirodho, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When their relishing ceases, grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "mn38:40.6"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya41
msgctxt "mn38:41.1"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:41.2"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:41.3"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:41.4"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:41.5"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme na sārajjati, appiyarūpe dhamme na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyasati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr "When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they don’t desire it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "mn38:41.6"
msgid "tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn38:41.7"
msgid "So evaṃ anurodhavirodhavippahīno yaṃ kiñci vedanaṃ vedeti, sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā, so taṃ vedanaṃ nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "Having given up favoring and opposing, when they experience any kind of feeling—pleasant, unpleasant, or neutral—they don’t approve, welcome, or keep clinging to it. "

msgctxt "mn38:41.8"
msgid "Tassa taṃ vedanaṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato yā vedanāsu nandī sā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "As a result, relishing of feelings ceases. "

msgctxt "mn38:41.9"
msgid "Tassa nandīnirodhā upādānanirodho, upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When their relishing ceases, grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "mn38:41.10"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Given that it occurs quite a few times, I take the phrase sankhittena tanhasankhayavimutti as an idiom referring to the brief statement made at the beginning, as also in MN 37.
msgctxt "mn38:41.11"
msgid "Imaṃ kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, saṅkhittena taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttiṃ dhāretha, sātiṃ pana bhikkhuṃ kevaṭṭaputtaṃ mahātaṇhājālataṇhāsaṅghāṭappaṭimukkan”ti. "
msgstr "Mendicants, you should memorize that brief statement on freedom through the ending of craving. But the mendicant Sāti, the fisherman’s son, is caught in a vast net of craving, a tangle of craving.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc110
msgctxt "mn38:41.12"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn38:41.13"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn38:41.14"
msgid "Mahātaṇhāsaṅkhayasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

